Package ontology.actions

Actions can be thought of as formal Message definitions that are sent between agents in the network.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConnectResponse
    YES or NO from the Super Peer
    FileList
    A list of filenames, to be sent to a super peer for indexing.
    FileRequest
    Asks a peer to reply with the file.
    FileResponse
    Simulates the transfer of a file.
    NeighboursResponse
    Host Cache sends a list of Super Peers.
    NetworkStats
    A message sent to the Runner with a bunch of information about the peer, for statistics collection.
    RequestConnect
    Peers ask Super Peers if they can connect.
    RequestNeighbours
    Asks for some Super Peer IDs, and adds the sender to the host cache.
    RequestSearch
    Search request for a file.
    SearchResponse
    When a file is found, this message is sent back to the original requester.
